{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Didn't know that it was Birkenau, but learned it subsequently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What happened there-- first, we were taken into a huge hall, which was the shower.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But prior to that, we were stripped naked, and our hair shorn everywhere-- pubic, everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember the yells.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At this point, there were German female guards called Aufseherinnens-- husky, blonde, Brunhildes screaming, yelling, whipping with whip.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The whip is in their hand.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember the one thing I wasn't going to let go of was my baccalaureate diploma, and it was in a green sort of a book.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Stripped naked, shorn, and I was clinging to it just like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And an Aufseherinnen saw that, and she just ripped it out of my hands, and it flew on the floor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Somebody picked it up, and it was in the garbage pile.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I began to just cry, sob, and it was partly the baccalaureate diploma, because I believe that underneath, without being conscious of that, I felt this was the last stripping away of my identity.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If they are taking this away from me as well, I'm alone.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've been separated from my family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They have cut my hair, and I had very long hair in those days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember feeling the hair sort of flowing down my back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember it was almost a sensuous feeling as I remembered how the hair, the long hair was cut.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What else can they do to me?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They are taking away my last contact with someone that I was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so I began screaming, yelling.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
